Date-Holidays-FR
================

USAGE
.....

  use Date::Holidays::FR;
  my ($year, $month, $day) = (localtime)[5, 4, 3];
  $year  += 1900;
  $month +=    1;
  print "Woohoo" if is_fr_holiday($year, $month, $day);

  my $day_off = holidays($year);
  for my $mmdd (sort keys  %$day_off) {
    print "$mmdd $day_off->{$mmdd}\n";
  }

INSTALLATION
............

To install this module, use the CPAN shell or cpanminus

Or you can type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES
............

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  Date::Easter
  Time::Local
  Readonly

